texts.text: >Somewhere in the city...
>The Liberators receive a request to join an investigation.
>They arrive late at night.
This should be the place.
Yep, I get a bad vibe just standin' here.
So, is this the underworld miasma you told us about, Saara?
Yes, and that is the source.
>Saara points to a small, gelatinous distortion ahead.
That space is a link between this world and the underworld.
If nothing is done, it will allow infernal fiends to invade.
If this is here, then...
It's still small, and there's no evidence of invaders yet.
My apologies, but I've requested your help for caution's sake.
No worries, Saara—no, Big Sis Apsaras!
"Big Sis"?
"Apsaras"?
Have you forgotten, Newbie?
Renowned meteorologist Saara Mizuno's true form...
...is the demon Apsaras.
She helped us in the battle against Vritra, remember?
No, it is I who should thank you.
A weather girl-slash-exorcist? You're one busy gal.
C'mon, let's give this hard-workin' demon one less job to do.
>The group stares at the twisted space in front of them.
So, how are we gonna shut this thing?
I will perform a purification dance.
It should sever the link and eliminate the distortion.
Big Sis Apsaras is gonna dance?!
I'll burn it into my memory! Teehee, what a feast for the eyes.
Um, it's just meant to fix the twist in time not—
Right, let us begin...
Huh?! What is this sensation...?!
Somethin' wrong?
...Oh no! Here it comes!
>The distortion quickly expands,
>and a single demon appears.
...So, I have returned to this world at last.
What?! You're...!
Indrajit!
Ah. It's been a while, accursed Liberators.
Never thought we'd see YOU again.
Between that time in the spiritual world
and Lord Asura's ceremony, I'm getting sick of your mug.
You wouldn't be so bold if you knew my hatred, humans.
After you defeated me, I fell into the underworld.
Yet my deep bitterness towards you has not diminished.
I've waited for our worlds to link. Now, I'll have my revenge.
You're resentful even in death. It's borderline obsessive.
Indrajit... So, you're behind this distortion...
In that case...!
I shall defeat you in Lord Indra's stead!
Ah, Apsaras. How brainless of you to befriend humans.
Idiot! The only one with no brains here is you!
Don't you recall who beat your ass last time?
Allow us to jog your memory!
>Megakin and the rest summon their demon allies.
As if I'd ever forget my past grievances...
I'll clear them away here!
>Indrajit closes the space between them in a single bound.
What, you think we'll run from a few fightin' words?
Hold on, somethin's off...
Too late. You've already fallen into my trap.
Embrace death.
>Indrajit fires a single arrow into the sky.
>It multiples into an endless stream that starts to rain down.
What?! A shower of arrows?!
Humans like you won't survive!
So, I have no choice!
>Apsaras transforms herself into a curtain of water.
>Her wall stops the incoming arrows.
Ugh!
Big Sis Apsaras!
Get inside a building! Hurry!!
>They run for their lives,
>but the curtain breaks halfway.
>The Liberators fail to escape and lose their demon allies.
Our allies...
Shit, this guy is bad news...
*Wince*
Megakin! Your arm...!
Heh... Guess I screwed up.
Even Apsaras had to stretch herself thin to save us...
This is my current strength.
My previous failure incited me to exceed my own limits.
Now, no one can protect you.
Ngh...
Everyone! Please run away!
What?!
>A hand rises from a puddle and grabs Indrajit's leg.
Now's your chance! Hurry!
That hand! It's Apsaras!
Megakin! We're...!
Sorry, but we need to fall back!
Indrajit...!
Yo, this ain't over yet!
Looks like we got away.
Yeah, but that was a hot mess.
And Apsaras...
I'm...fine...
Big Sis Apsaras!
I was able to...escape somehow...
But the situation is still dire...
Yeah, he must on the hunt for ritual sacrifices again.
We'll need to devise a counter-measure to avoid another failure.
Still, that strength means big trouble.
Then, let's ask for "his" cooperation.
"His"?
Lukewarm firepower from a nobody won't do jack shit.
No, this individual was once worshipped as king of the gods.
His power is immense, and he has deep ties to Indrajit.
...So, who we talkin' about here?
My lord...
Indra.
Have you forgotten, Newbie?
